summary:
10. Condemns ceasefire agreement violations; 

11. Welcomes decreased tensions in Kodori Valley; 

12. Requests Georgian side to improve security for joint patrols; 

13. Urges parties to revitalize the peace process.
The Security Council:

* Calls on both parties to build on the Yalta meeting on confidence-building measures and implement proposals in a purposeful and cooperative manner (para 13);
* Stresses the urgent need for progress on refugees and internally displaced persons, and reaffirms their inalienable right to return to their homes in secure and dignified conditions (para 14);
* Urges parties to implement recommendations on the Gali district and for the Abkhaz side to improve law enforcement and address education concerns (para 15);
* Calls on parties to dissociate themselves from militant rhetoric and support for military options (para 16);
* Welcomes additional safeguards for helicopter flights and calls on parties to identify and bring to justice those responsible for the shooting down of a UNOMIG helicopter (para 17);
* Underlines the primary responsibility of both sides to provide security and ensure freedom of movement for UNOMIG and other international personnel (para 18);
* Welcomes UNOMIG's review of its security arrangements (para 19);
* Extends UNOMIG's mandate until 31 July 2003 and requests a report from the Secretary-General three months from the adoption of this resolution (paras 20-21);
* Decides to remain actively seized of the matter (para 22).
